100,000 supply chain disruption events across 5 industries (Automotive, Electronics, Pharmaceuticals, Consumer Goods, Aerospace)
Tracks disruptions across multi-tier supplier networks (Tier 1-4), not just direct suppliers
Covers 6 disruption types: Natural disasters, Cyberattacks, Geopolitical issues, Labor strikes, Port congestion, Factory incidents
Includes severity levels, production impact %, financial losses, and response strategies
Measures both partial and full recovery timelines
Features realistic correlations (e.g., backup suppliers → faster recovery, higher severity → permanent supplier changes)
